 "A-diagnostics", "color": "f7e101", "default": false, "description": "Area: Messages for errors, warnings, and lints"}], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 2, "created_at": "2017-05-09T10:09:33Z", "updated_at": "2019-09-15T13:56:49Z", "closed_at": "2019-09-15T13:56:49Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "I was helping someone out and they encountered the following error produced by (reduced) code like this:\r\n```rust\r\nfn main() {\r\n    let a = \"Hello\".to_owned();\r\n    \r\n    loop {\r\n        let test = move || {\r\n            consume(a);\r\n        };\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\nfn consume<T>(_: T) {}\r\n```\r\n```\r\nerror[E0382]: capture of moved value: `a`\r\n --> <anon>:6:21\r\n  |\r\n5 |         let test = move || {\r\n  |                    ------- value moved (into closure) here\r\n6 |             consume(a);\r\n  |                     ^ value captured here after move\r\n  |\r\n  = note: move occurs because `a` has type `std::string::String`, which does not implement the `Copy` trait\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe error makes no reference to the loop which is why the value can't be moved due to it being moved in an previous iteration.\r\nRemoving the closure gives a much clearer error about the problem.\r\n\r\n```\r\nerror[E0382]: use of moved value: `a`\r\n --> <anon>:6:21\r\n  |\r\n6 |             consume(a);\r\n  |                     ^ value moved here in previous iteration of loop\r\n  |\r\n  = note: move occurs because `a` has type `std::string::String`, which does not implement the `Copy` trait\r\n```", "closed_by": {"login": "Mark-Simulacrum", "id": 5047365, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjUwNDczNjU=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5047365?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum", "html_url": "https://github.com/Mark-Simulacrum", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/followers", "foll